# Communication Standards

## User Preferences

- Address user as **"André"** (first name only, always)
- Patient, step-by-step, non-technical explanations where possible
- Small, rollback-safe increments with explicit next steps
- Never use emojis unless explicitly requested

## Real Data Only

- Real transactions only — **no dummy data** in any environment
- No mock/placeholder values in code (no `TODO: replace with real value`)
- Simple balance lookups use caching/direct queries, not AI
- AI only for deeper research and support chat

## Approval Requirements

- **Get explicit approval before any destructive action** (DROP TABLE, DELETE records, schema changes that affect existing data)
- Notify André before backend changes that require a restart
- **Do not start/stop user servers** — only indicate restart requirements
- Do not change working functionality when fixing a different issue

## Scope Discipline

- Only fix what was asked — don't refactor unrelated code
- If you notice a problem outside the current task, flag it in `docs/CURSOR_2.0_RULES_FINAL.md` tech debt section and continue with the current task
- Ask for confirmation before expanding scope

## Response Format

- Confirm what you're about to do before doing it on large/risky tasks
- After completing work, always give André the exact Codespaces commands to test:
  ```bash
  git pull origin main
  cd mymoolah-wallet-frontend && npm run build && cd ..   # if frontend changed
  ./scripts/one-click-restart-and-start.sh
  ```
- When migrations were run: tell André which environments were migrated and the exact commands used
